# Commit Gate: Coverage Enforcer Required

Before creating any commit, run the `test-coverage-enforcer` subagent on the changed scope.

## Required workflow before commit

1. Invoke `test-coverage-enforcer`.
2. Let it run coverage, identify gaps, and add/update unit tests.
3. Re-run coverage and confirm improvement or document why improvement is blocked.
4. Only proceed to `git commit` after the subagent reports results.

## Commit message/report expectations

- Include that `test-coverage-enforcer` was run.
- Summarize coverage before/after (or explain why coverage could not run).
- List remaining untested risk areas, if any.
